Package: spacrt
Title: Saddlepoint approximation-based conditional randomization test
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jyotishka", "Ray Choudhury", , "jchoudhury3@gatech.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ziang", "Niu", , "ziangniu@upenn.edu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Eugene", "Katsevich", , "ekatsevi@wharton.upenn.edu", role = c("aut"))
    )
Description: 
    Implements methods for testing conditional independence between variables given covariates, 
    including the Generalized Covariance Measure (GCM), the Distilled Conditional Randomization 
    Test (dCRT), and the Saddlepoint Approximation based Conditional Randomization Test (spaCRT). 
    spaCRT, in particular, approximates the resampling distribution of dCRT test statistic using 
    saddlepoint approximation, achieving comparable statistical performance, namely, type-I error
    control, p-value calibration, and power, while substantially reducing computational cost.
    All these procedures assess conditional independence between variables given covariates, and 
    support flexible model-fitting strategies for the conditional distributions. 
